flowRoot.flowPara: Thoba Lose, Peter van Heusden, Alan Christoffels
Storing biological data involves modeling and storing thousands of entities that are interrelated in complex ways.
Relational databases are meet very specific needs and are not designed to fit all scenarios.
Graph databases are seen as a natural fit to this complex network.
Neo4j is a highly scalable database with a declarative query language called Cypher.
We implemented a GIE to explore the Neo4j database
